The paper presents an algorithm for differentially private learning of parameters in directed graphical models, which is a topic related to machine learning and privacy. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with sensitive domains such as medical diagnostics, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The algorithm presented in the paper is data-dependent and optimized for the properties of the private input dataset and the graph structure of the DGM, which indicates that it may be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the use of noise in the algorithm, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory).
